  <div class="row">
    <div class="twelve columns">
      <h3 class="subheader">The sign-up complains my e-mail address isn't valid</h3>
      <p>Currently, the system is limited to academic users. This means that
      all e-mail addresses used during sign-up must end with <tt>.edu</tt> or
      <tt>.ac.<em>country</em></tt> (where country is something like
      <tt>uk</tt> or <tt>fr</tt>, etc.)</p>
      <p>Once the system is out of beta, we will extend it to permit paying
      users to sign-up with any e-mail address. For academic users, the system
      will always remain free.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <span metal:use-macro="view.master.footer"></span>
